            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@da-woods totally hear you, but as it stands, the `3.0.10` release is producing broken C code.\r\n\r\nIn particular the `cython` CLI is adding in code based on the `Cython/Includes/numpy/__init__.pxd` file even though I haven't explicitly asked for it. The `_speedup.c` file in https://github.com/dhermes/bezier is produced with no flags at all:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncython src/python/bezier/_speedup.pyx\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf there is a way to tell the `cython` CLI to **exclude** `Cython/Includes/numpy/`, I'd happily use that.\r\n\r\nGiven the removal of `numpy/__init__.pxd` in https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5842, is there any reason why you wouldn't do a `3.1.x` release?\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nI.e. is there a straightforward way I could control:\r\n\r\n```c\r\n/* #### Code section: filename_table ### */\r\n\r\nstatic const char *__pyx_f[] = {\r\n  \"src/python/bezier/_speedup.pyx\",\r\n  \"<stringsource>\",\r\n  \"Cython/Includes/numpy/__init__.pxd\",\r\n  \"Cython/Includes/cpython/type.pxd\",\r\n};\r\n```",
